verbs.description: redescend (third-person singular simple present redescends, present participle redescending, simple past and past participle redescended)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To descend again (often following an ascent)
examples: To thee sweet Spirit I return
That love wherwith my heart doth burn,
And these bless’d notions of my brain
I now breath up to thee again,
O let them redescend, and still
My soul with holy raptures fill.
